HEADWORD: Ruba-dub
<hw>Rub"a-dub</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The sound of a drum
when continuously beaten; hence, a clamorous, repeated sound; a
clatter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>rubadub</qex> of the abolition presses.</q> <rj><qau>D.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rubaiyat</ent>⟦br⟧
